V(J3/5) = V(A3/5) + JA*w3/5 From vector to module: V(J3/5) = V(A3/5) + JA*w3/5
Then, JA*IA*w3/5 = JA*OA*w4/5 - JA*IO*w2/5 = IA*JO*w1/5 - IA*OA*w4/5
We consider that the gear-modules are equal: m2 = (=m31) equal to m1 (=m32)
If Z32=Z31, then Z1=Z2+2*Z3 and Z3 = (Z1-Z2)/2
So, to get R4/2 = 1/R, Z3 = Z2*(R/2-1)
